#Global Requirements
This document's aim is to identify needs and requirements from all the OSX products that are using a common html file and common CSS styling

##general 
Take specific formats into account (webview, epub, pdf, Tutor)

##PDF styles/framework
Maintainablity: 
  - lifetime (natural evolution of code base over time)
  - multiple users, code consistency
  - future development (features, refactor)
  
Ease of use: 
  - efficient to use: clear file structure, clear logic pathways, 
  - tailored to PDF(print) specific needs 
  - minimal regression testing
  
Fast creation
  - DRY code
  - reusable/modular when creating/updating templates

